f:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Binance calculates SUI/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using a time-weighted average of the premium between perpetual and spot prices. Long positions pay funding when rates are positive, while shorts receive payments, with settlements occurring automatically without affecting position sizes. The funding rate is capped at ±2% per 8-hour period, though SUI typically exhibits lower volatility with rates ranging between -0.5% to +1.5%. Binance's deep liquidity ensures minimal slippage during funding settlement periods, crucial for maintaining hedge ratios in arbitrage strategies."}]
10:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","SUI","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SUI/USDT represents an attractive funding arbitrage target due to its position as a high-performance L1 blockchain with significant institutional interest but moderate retail speculation. The pair exhibits consistent funding rate patterns driven by SUI's proof-of-stake mechanics and growing DeFi ecosystem, creating predictable arbitrage windows. Binance's SUI/USDT market depth typically exceeds $10M within 2% of mid-price, enabling large arbitrage positions without significant market impact."}]]}]
11:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SUI/USDT funding rates on Binance have historically skewed positive during network upgrade periods and negative during broader crypto market downturns. The pair shows distinct patterns around SUI ecosystem developments, with rates spiking to +1.2% during major DeFi protocol launches on the network. Weekly analysis reveals funding rates correlate strongly with SUI staking rewards announcements and validator set changes. The 30-day rolling average typically ranges between -0.1% to +0.4%, with standard deviation of 0.6%, indicating moderate volatility suitable for systematic arbitrage strategies. Peak funding periods often coincide with increased on-chain activity and gas fee spikes on the SUI network."}]]}]
12:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunity Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Binance's SUI/USDT perpetual offers compelling arbitrage setups when funding rates exceed ±0.8% annualized, particularly during SUI ecosystem catalysts. The optimal strategy involves shorting perpetuals while holding SUI spot during positive funding periods, capturing 8-hour payments while maintaining delta neutrality. Cross-exchange arbitrage opportunities frequently emerge between Binance and OKX, with funding rate differentials reaching 0.3-0.5% during high volatility periods. Risk-adjusted returns improve significantly when combining funding arbitrage with basis trading during SUI futures expiration weeks. The pair's moderate correlation with major altcoins (0.65 with ETH) provides portfolio diversification benefits for multi-asset funding strategies."}]]}]
13:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SUI/USDT funding arbitrage on Binance requires careful monitoring of the network's validator dynamics and potential consensus issues that could trigger emergency stops. The pair's moderate liquidity means large positions above $5M notional may face increased slippage during rapid market moves or funding settlements. Binance's cross-margin system can amplify risks if SUI experiences sudden depegging from fundamental issues, requiring isolated margin for pure arbitrage strategies. Auto-deleveraging risk increases during extreme funding periods when long/short imbalances exceed 80%, particularly common during SUI staking reward distributions. Position sizing should account for Binance's 20% initial margin requirement and potential for funding rate caps to activate during black swan events affecting the Sui blockchain infrastructure."}]]}]
14:["$","$L16",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often do SUI/USDT funding rates update on Binance?","answer":"Binance updates SUI/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. The rates are calculated using the previous 8-hour time-weighted average premium between perpetual and index prices, with settlements automatically processed at each interval."},{"question":"What's the typical funding rate range for SUI/USDT on Binance?","answer":"SUI/USDT funding rates on Binance typically range from -0.5% to +1.5% per 8-hour period, with a long-term average around +0.2%. During major SUI network events or broader crypto volatility, rates can reach the ±2% cap, though this occurs less than 5% of the time."},{"question":"Can I trade SUI/USDT perpetuals with leverage on Binance?","answer":"Yes, Binance offers up to 25x leverage on SUI/USDT perpetuals with a minimum 20% initial margin requirement. For funding arbitrage strategies, most traders use 1x-5x leverage to maintain lower liquidation risk while capturing funding payments effectively."},{"question":"How does Binance calculate the SUI/USDT index price?","answer":"Binance calculates the SUI/USDT index price using a weighted average from multiple spot exchanges including Binance spot, Coinbase, and Kraken. The index updates every second and serves as the reference for funding rate calculations, ensuring the perpetual tracks the underlying SUI spot market accurately."}]}]
